events.name: Google Certification for Web Developers
events.description:
*********
RSVP/Register at: https://peatix.com/event/375447
*********

The Mobile Sites (mSite) certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals, who demonstrate proficiency in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development. A Mobile Sites certification allows individuals to demonstrate that Google recognizes them as an expert in mobile sites.

Agenda:
1-3 pm : Study Jam led by mSite Certified facilitators.
3-5 pm : Attempt the free certification exam.

Important Note:
1. Bring your own laptop
2. You need basic web development skills
3. Study Jam is suitable for programmer with minimum of 3-6 months of experience in building web sites.
3. Study Jam is focus on basic concepts. So may not be suitable for very experienced programmers.

events.name: Android Application Profiling - CodeLab
events.description:
Welcome to this 2:30Hrs instructor lead codelab/hands-on session, you'll learn how to use Android Debugging and Profiling tools, to improve your application performance.

What we'll do
- Intro about Debugging & Profiling Tools (Part of SDK and External)
- Share the Sample Application for Testing
- Hands-On: Session, Network and Energy Profiling

What you'll learn
- How to configure and profile an Android Application
- How to collect, view and analyze the Profiling data.

What you'll need
- Laptop with Latest Android Studio and SDK
- Basic understanding of the Android Application Programming
- An Android Device or Emulator running Android Oreo(8.0) or later

Instructors: Ms Renu and Mr Sachin from Grab.
Join in, get tickets ($5) now on our peatix page: https://peatix.com/event/437114

events.name: DevFest 2018
events.description:
DevFest Talks:

Registration: 9.30 AM onwards.

1. TensorFlow Extended: An end-to-end ML platform - Chuan Yu Foo (Google)
2. Recap of Android Dev Summit 2018 - Hassan Abid (GDE)
3. UX/UI Design Talk - Priyanka (Google)

==> Lunch Break (~12:15 - 1:00 PM)

4. Recent Updates in Kotlin - Stepan (Kotlin-SG)
5. Service Management with Istio on Google Kubernetes Engines - Nikit Swaraj
6. Get Started Data Studio - Khairul (Sparkline)

==> Afternoon Break (~3:15 - 3:30 PM)

7. Digital Marketing Life Cycle - Kushal (Shoppee)
8. Build native web components that can use to any JS framework or library - Arjay Elbore

Wrap-up: 5.45pm

GDG DevFests are large, community-run developer events happening around the globe focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies. Each DevFest is inspired by and uniquely tailored to the needs of the local developer community. DevFest powered by a shared belief that when developers come together to exchange ideas, amazing things can happen.

GDG DevFest 2018 is our annual all-day developer conference that offers speaker sessions across multiple product areas and more! It is the biggest Google related developer event in Singapore, carefully crafted for you by your GDG.

events.name: Firebase Summit Extended 2018 - Singapore
events.description:
Firebase Summit Extended 2018 is an event which allows communities to come together and learn about Firebase and help teams of all sizes across the entire development life cycle, from building their app, to improve app quality, to growing their business.

Agenda:
1:00 PM - Registration
1:30 PM - Building Serverless Application - Jerome Poudevigne (Google)
2:15 PM - Smarter segmentation with Audiences and Predictions - Aditya Gautam (Google)

3:00 PM - Break (~3PM to 3:15PM)

3:15 PM - MLKit - Jason Zaman (GDG-SG)
4:00 PM - Go Serverless! Managing Payments - Lauren Long (Google)
4:45 PM - YTBD (Google Speaker)

The Firebase Summit happened Oct 29 in Prague.
https://firebase.google.com/summit/
